# DRY and logic placement

## DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself)

- Never duplicate logic (task IDs, commands, config paths, `run_once` invocations)
- If two or more places need the same logic, extract a shared function
- When a `run_once` task is started in one place and peeked/waited in another, the start command must live in ONE shared helper -- not copy-pasted

## Logic belongs in ABA core, not the TUI

- ABA core (`scripts/include_all.sh`, dedicated scripts, Makefile targets) owns the smarts
- The TUI is a dumb consumer: it calls ABA functions/commands, orchestrates UI (dialogs, infoboxes), and reads results
- Never add business logic, caching logic, or data-fetching logic directly in TUI code
- Pattern: ABA core function does the work -> TUI fires it via `run_once` -> TUI peeks/waits/reads output
